translated: Janson, Robert, archdeacon, Gothenburg, born on October 9th, 1874 in Gothenburg, son of J. A. J. and Lovisa Törnsten. Married in 1903 to Anna Maria Svensson. Children: Ake, born in 1907, minister, Sverker, born in 1908, PhD in Philosophy, Inga, born in 1910, gymnasium director, married to Hedelin, Eskil, born in 1911, bank clerk, Ragnar, born in 1912, veterinarian, Gösta, born in 1914, watchmaker, Anna-Maja, born in 1916, gymnasium director, married to Kiälkot. Earned Mog. ex. in Gothenburg in 1893, Philosophy Diploma in 1895, theoretical theology diploma, practical theology diploma in 1898, ordained priest for the Gothenburg diocese in 1899. Assistant pastor in the Gothenburg Cathedral Parish in 1903, church assistant there in 1904, minister there since 1908, and archdeacon in the southern archdeaconry of the cathedral since 1939. Member of the Royal Order of the North Star (LNO).
